  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kenya Apis Enterprise - Increasing Incomes of Small Scale Bee Keepers</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to not only increase incomes of rural honey producers, but most importantly to offer a platform for women and youth to enter the business and an income as well. Moreover, the aim of the project is to give rural producers an economic stake into a profitable enterprise</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will work to support the set-up of Honey Hub Enterprises in four counties; 

The hubs will act as trading points for small scale producers to be able to access extension service, market for their hive products as well as a point of linkage to access financial capital to increase incomes into their apis trade

To do this actions of both soft and infrastructural geared towards establishing a business will be undertaken, as well as linking farmers and other stakeholders to trade with the hub, and most importantly work towards a unifiying farmer aggregating body (co-operative) to enable farmers own shares in the hub</narrative>
  </description>
